
LATEST VERSION
==============

Before going further, you can check that this package you have is
the latest version by checking the exiflow download page at:

    http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=151136


EXECUTION REQUIREMENTS
======================

Running exiflow requires Python version 2.4 or later and the following 
toolkits and modules:

 -- ExifTool by Phil Harvey for reading and writing exif informations 
     in image files  (http://www.sno.phy.queensu.ca/~phil/exiftool/)

 -- python-gtk2  (http://www.daa.com.au/~james/software/pygtk/)

 -- python-glade2  (http://www.daa.com.au/~james/software/pygtk/)


RECOMMENDATIONS
===============

In this first step exiflow is designed to work together with gthumb
as image viewer and browser (http://gthumb.sourceforge.net/)


INSTALLATION REQUIREMENTS
=========================

Installing exiflow from this package requires the Python distutils
package which are part from Python2.4. 

INSTALLATION
============

Your options are:

    --  (Recommended.)  Install from a pre-packaged exiflow package that
        does not require distutils:

            Red Hat Linux / SuSE  exiflow-x.x.x-1.noarch.rpm

            Debian GNU/Linux    exiflow_x.x.x-1_all.deb

    --  (Optional.)  Install from this source package.
    
        Assuming your system satisfies the installation requirements in the
        previous section, install exiflow from this package simply by 
	running the provided Python-standard setup script as follows:

        # python2.4 setup.py install

        By default, the above command will do the following:

	--  Install the "exiflow" scripts in the default system script 
	    directory (/usr/bin for example). 
	
	--  Install the "exiflow" python module in the standard Python
	    library directory (/usr/lib/python2.4/site-packages for example).
	


